Taiwanese Stocks: China Airlines, Nan Ya Plastics, Yulon Motor

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-11-28T06:20:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-28/taiwan-stocks-china-airlines-nan-ya-plastics-yulon-motor.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (TWSE)  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are at the close in Taipei trading.  The Taiex Index rose 1.7 percent to 6,898.78, the biggest
increase since Nov. 14.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT) surged 6.9 percent to NT$13.90
and  Chimei Innolux Corp. (3481)  (3481 TT) jumped 6.7 percent to
NT$12.70. The Economic Daily News reported Chinese manufacturer
TCL Corp. will purchase more than $1 billion of flat panels,
components, home appliances and other products from the
companies.  China Airlines Ltd. (2610)  (2610 TT) gained 1.2 percent to
NT$12.95. The island’s largest carrier has filled almost 90
percent of its capacity for flights over the Lunar New Year
season, the Commercial Times reported, without saying where it
got the information. Hamilton Liu, spokesman for the company,
wasn’t immediately available for comment.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT) lost 3.7 percent to NT$471.50. The
smartphone maker withdrew its appeal against a patent ruling won
by IPCom GmbH & Co. in Germany. The bid was no longer necessary
after a separate German patent court partly invalidated the
patent at issue, HTC’s lawyer Martin Chakraborty said in an
interview.  Yulon Motor Co. (2201)  (2201 TT) increased 3.7 percent to
NT$59.50. The company said it plans to invest $150 million to
form a new investment unit in  China .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
